rename.from: ci: TensorFlow doesn't work with numpy
rename.to: ci: TensorFlow 2.3.0 doesn't work with numpy 1.19.1

body:
We tried pinning tensorflow to < 2.3.0 but no relief yet.

This issue https://github.com/pypa/pip/issues/8076 captures some of what the core problem is here. Ideally we'd have some sort of per-package virtualenv.

To focus on the matter at hand though, we need to understand what package is causing a onflicting version range and see if we can do something similar to what was done with scipy

Hi @pdxjohnny
This issue is still going on: https://github.com/tensorflow/models/issues/9200
Workaround is to either use tensorflow 2.2 or pin numpy to some version <1.19.1
Few day back I tried pinning it to 1.18.5, it seems to be working: https://github.com/0dust/dffml/tree/resolve_tf_conflict_with_np
